1	Use Case [#]:  [Register User Account]
1.1	Description
The Customer decides to register a user account before purchasing a specific service from the online catalog for delivery.
1.2	Level
High Level
1.3	Trigger
The Customer clicks the purchase link.
1.4	Primary Actor
The Primary Actor is the Customer shopping the Company’s online catalog.
1.5	Additional/Supporting Actors
Secondary Actors: 
•	Online Chat Assistant/Tech Support
•	Account Representative
1.6	Stakeholders 
Stakeholders:
•	Accounts Receivable department
•	Order Picking department
•	Shipping department
1.7	Preconditions
The Customer must have an active internet connection, logged onto the site open in the browser.
1.8	Main Success Scenario
1.	Customer chooses a product.
2.	Online Assistant contacts customer.
3.	Customer declines assistance.
4.	The system sends a message customer to register or login before moving forward.
5.	The customer registers or Logs in
6.	Customer enters payment and shipping information.
7.	The system responds.
8.	The customer confirms purchase.

1.9	Extensions
1.	Exception: Login details are incorrect:
1.	System displays a warning message
2.	The Customer re-enters correct information.
3.	The System responds.

1.	Alternative: The customer inputs email information to change password.
1.	System confirms the email from the database.
2.	System processes data.
3.	Customer re-news their password. 
4.	System sends confirmation.

1.10	Post Conditions
1.10.1	Success End Condition
The customer receives a registration confirmation.
The customer receives an order confirmation. 
The admin confirms a payment transaction.
 
1.10.2	Minimal Guarantees
1.10.3	Failure End Condition
The customer fails to register an account and fails to make the purchase.

1.11	Frequency
Once

1.12	Special Requirements
1.12.1	Performance
The customer should be taken to the order confirmation screen with 10 seconds of entering payment information after registering or logging into their user account.

1.12.2	Security
Customer’s password will be masked in the display.
 
1.12.3	Usability / Accessibility

Customer must be able to view page in English.

1.12.4	Other

1.13	Issues and Next Steps

